5|$|In <b>the</b> <b>Truman</b> Study is a {{fireplace}} mantel that was originally {{installed in the}} White House. It was removed to Blair House during Truman's occupancy, when he used this room as his personal office. In 1987, the mantel was refinished in white enamel with gold-leaf accents. In 2004, before the state funeral of Ronald Reagan, Nancy Reagan used <b>the</b> <b>Truman</b> Study to receive visitors.|$|E
