5000|$|In {{the churchyard}} is a {{tombstone}} on which is engraved the following Crest, [...] "A dragon's head erased, &c.," [...] which tombstone {{is said to}} have been erected on one of <b>the</b> <b>Trumans</b> of Llantrisant, who were descended from the Herberts of Pembroke, and <b>the</b> <b>Trumans</b> of Northampton. Some of the family are now resident in the district. Also there can be seen on a headstone near the tower the inscription recording the death of one David Jenkins, who lived to the advanced age of 107.|$|R
